'''Richard Baker''' is a retired makeup artist who worked in the second production unit for [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']], and served as creature supervisor for the cantina sequence in ''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]''.<ref name="Starlog 19">Millar, Natalie. "''Star Wars'' Invades TV", [[Starlog (magazine)|''Starlog'']] #19, February 1979, p. 50</ref>

He has won six Academy Awards, out of eleven nominations, for the films ''An American Werewolf in London'' (1981), ''Harry and the Hendersons'' (1988), ''Ed Wood'' (1994), ''The Nutty Professor'' (1996), ''Men in Black'' (1997), and ''How the Grinch Stole Christmas'' (2000). Baker also worked on another [[Lucasfilm]] production, [[Wikipedia:Captain EO|''Captain EO'']], directed by Francis Ford Coppola and released in [[1986]] for the [[The Walt Disney Company|Disney]] Theme Parks.

